==English==

===Noun===

'''piker'''

# a person who [[bet]]s or [[gamble]]s with small amounts of [[money]]
# a [[cheapskate]]

It has been linked etymologically to the word '''[[pikey]]'''{{ref|bloomsbury}} as well as to [[w:Pike County, Missouri|Pike County]] in eastern [[w:Missouri]] [http://www.yourdictionary.com/ahd/p/p0300200.html]. In the latter instance the term originally denoted poor immigrants to [[w:California]].

The 2000 film ''[[w:Boiler Room]]'' makes reference to "pikers" in the following excerpt:

:''So now you know what's possible, let me tell you what's required. You are required to work your fucking ass off at this firm. We want winners here, not '''pikers'''. A '''piker''' walks at the bell. A '''piker''' asks how much vacation time you get in the first year. Vacation time? People come to work at this firm for one reason: to become filthy rich; that's it. We're not here to make friends; we're not saving the fucking manatees here, guys. You want vacation time, go teach third grade at a public school.'' ([http://www.moviewavs.com/cgi-bin/moviewavs.cgi?Boiler_Room=whatsrequired.wav wav], [http://www.moviewavs.com/cgi-bin/mp3s.cgi?Boiler_Room=whatsrequired.mp3 mp3])

